<p>NATO defense ministers met Wednesday in Brussels to address a spate of airspace violations and mysterious drone incursions while drumming up more military support for Ukraine amid a sharp drop in Western weapons deliveries [france24.com#1][dw.com#1][euronews.com#1][japantoday.com#1]. Recent incidents include suspicious UAVs violating Belgian, German, Danish and Norwegian airspace, Russian drones tracked over Romania and shot down over Poland, and NATO jets dispatched after three Russian MiG-31s loitered in Estonian airspace for 12 minutes [politico.eu#1]. To plug gaps, NATO has unveiled an Eastern Sentry program to shift warplanes and air defense systems to frontline allies, while ministers debate whether national &quot;caveats&quot; are constraining the alliance’s top commander [politico.eu#1]. Washington is weighing the supply of longer-range Tomahawk missiles to Kyiv and expects allies to announce &quot;big&quot; spending pledges for Ukrainian weapons purchases at the meeting [france24.com#1][politico.eu#1].</p><img src='https://kagiproxy.com/img/RGsjy7uhNUhxqWUh4WUW5MfsXhRsZEa4x4MHExr1M0Keu2J5q1BmDppoLnwMB8ksEtLhYVbyYk4uWwrLKYBqMhWxxQhPxU1yAB_8OKBOicL9bCuHjBdjyykJbt-qsGqCmdOCLLs_pLcavwVDtKnVddSmXXcp' alt='NATO defense ministers meet in Brussels amid airspace incursions and efforts to reinforce Ukraine’s defenses.' /><br /><h3>Highlights:</h3><ul><li>Airspace incidents: In recent weeks, suspicious drones violated Belgian, German, Danish and Norwegian airspace; Russian drones were tracked over Romania and shot down over Poland; and three Russian MiG-31s loitered 12 minutes in Estonian airspace [politico.eu#1].</li><li>Eastern Sentry: NATO’s new Eastern Sentry program shifts warplanes and air defense systems to frontline allies to improve coverage and responsiveness [politico.eu#1].</li><li>Ukraine support: Ministers focused on securing more weapons and ammunition for Kyiv amid a sharp drop in Western deliveries [japantoday.com#1][euronews.com#1].</li><li>Command authority: Allies debated how national &#x27;caveats&#x27; on forces may hinder SACEUR’s ability to respond rapidly to aerial threats [politico.eu#1].</li><li>US signals: Washington is considering longer-range Tomahawk missiles for Ukraine and expects &#x27;big&#x27; allied spending pledges for purchases at the meeting [france24.com#1][politico.eu#1].</li></ul><blockquote>It’s no secret that the more ‘national caveats’ there are on — especially our fighter jet assets — the harder it is for SACEUR to respond immediately. - Matthew Whitaker</blockquote><h3>Perspectives:</h3><ul><li>NATO: Publicly maintains it has sufficient authority to act against aerial threats despite debates over national caveats. (<a href='https://www.politico.eu/article/nato-weighs-options-to-sew-up-patchwork-air-defenses/'>Politico Europe</a>)</li><li>United States: Expects allies to unveil &#x27;big&#x27; spending pledges for Ukrainian weapons and is weighing provision of longer-range missiles. (<a href='https://www.politico.eu/article/nato-weighs-options-to-sew-up-patchwork-air-defenses/'>Politico Europe</a>)</li><li>United States: Is considering the supply of longer-range Tomahawk missiles to Kyiv as part of efforts to bolster Ukraine’s defenses. (<a href='https://www.france24.com/en/europe/20251015-nato-looks-to-bolster-air-defences-in-wake-of-russian-drone-incursions'>France 24</a>)</li></ul><h3>Sources:</h3><ul><li><a href='https://www.theguardian.com/world/live/2025/oct/15/russia-ukraine-nato-france-latest-europe-live-news-updates'>Nato looks to bolster defences in response to Russian air incursions – Europe live</a> - theguardian.com</li><li><a href='https://japantoday.com/category/world/nato-seeks-more-arms-for-ukraine-as-western-support-fades-and-allied-airspace-concerns-mount'>NATO seeks more arms for Ukraine as Western support fades and allied airspace concerns mount</a> - japantoday.com</li><li><a href='https://www.france24.com/en/europe/20251015-nato-looks-to-bolster-air-defence